  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean, bounded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Operating envelope is explicitly bounded: flow rates 1–7 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–5000 RPM, inlet pressure 5–15 mmHg, hematocrit 35–45%, temperature 36–38 °C, and impeller tip-clearance tolerance ±0.05 mm. Validation experiments densely cover the declared envelope at five flow-speed operating points. All 13 credibility factors assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels for the accepted decision. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed across all five operating points. Decision: Accepted.",
