    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels across the complete factor set. Operating envelope is explicitly bounded (1–7 L/min, 2000–5000 RPM, ±0.05 mm tip clearance) and validation experiments provide 94% interpolated coverage of the declared envelope. Monte Carlo UQ with 2000 samples propagates uncertainty through all primary inputs; 95% prediction intervals enclose all experimental means. Maximum NIH prediction error 14.3% is within the 20% acceptance criterion. GCI < 5% at all operating points. Independent peer review of simulation setup completed. Model form justified by three-model turbulence comparison. The combination of dense validation coverage, bounded and explicitly declared operating envelope, quantified uncertainty, and all factor gaps closed supports acceptance of the CFD model for predicting absolute hemolysis levels in the declared COU.",
